The paper discusses a security attack on temperature sensors used in critical systems such as infant incubators. This falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a new anomaly detector for temperature-based critical applications, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and embedded systems (cs.ET). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact on human health, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
